        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 1:14AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 114 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles east of Glazier, or 14 miles northeast of Canadian, moving
southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lipscomb, Canadian, Briscoe, Higgins, Lora, Allison, Glazier, and
Lake Marvin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
